column1: For every Emergency Department encounter, hospitals report a Principal Diagnosis and up to 24 Other Diagnoses.  The Diagnosis Code Frequency Report shows the frequency, in each position, of the reporting of each code.
ICD9CMCode = the diagnosis code (International Classification of Diseases, 9th Revision, Clinical Modification), effective for encounters prior to October 1, 2015.
ICD10CMCode = the diagnosis code (International Classification of Diseases, 10th Revision, Clinical Modification), effective for encounters beginning October 1, 2015.
TotalDiag = the total number of times the diagnosis code was reported in a Principal or Other Diagnosis position.
d0 = the total number of times the diagnosis code was reported as a Principal Diagnosis (i.e. chief cause of encounter).
d1-d24 = the total number of times the diagnosis code was reported in each Other Diagnosis position.
Data Source: California Emergency Department Database, Office of Statewide Health Planning and Development
